Introduction¶

About the Dataset

This Dataset contains information on 113,937 loans with 81 variables From Prosper Loan, a peer-to-peer personal loan 
lending Company.This Dataset will be explored To Help identify variables That are Pivotal In loan Completion

# reusable Function
def count_values(df='',lists=[''],sort=''):
    df_variables=df[lists]
    for column in df_variables.columns.values.tolist():
            print(column)
            print(df_variables[column].value_counts(sort=sort))
            print("")

# converting IncomeRange and EmploymentStatus To a Categorical variable
ordinal_var_dict = {'IncomeRange': ['$0','$1-24,999','$25,000-49,999','$50,000-74,999','$75,000-99,999','$100,000+','Not employed','Not displayed'],
                    'EmploymentStatus': ['Full-time', 'Part-time','Employed','Self-employed', 'Not employed', 'Retired', 'Other','Not available']}

for var in ordinal_var_dict:
    ordered_var = pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(ordered = True,
                                                categories = ordinal_var_dict[var])
    loan_var[var] = loan_var[var].astype(ordered_var)

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

 The Dataset Originally had a Dimenision of  113,937 Observations  with 81 variables,which was later subsetted to 55089 
 observations and 17 Variables.This Huge reduction in the Dataset in terms of Rows and Columns  is as a result of The 
 Objective of The Analysis,which is  to Determine The variables That Might help  predict The Outcome Of a 
 loan(Completed,ChargedOff,Defaulted,Cancelled)So as To Know which Loan applications are to be approved or Not .
 with over 58000 Observations still a running loan and Had to be Dropped .
 Amidst The 81 Variables,only a handful  of it seems to be pivotal to the aim of the Analysis and were picked .

The Selected Variables picked  for the analysis are :
  • ListingCreationDate: The Date the Loan application was put in.
  • LoanOriginationDate: The Date when The Loan application was approved
  • Term : Duration Of The loan In Months ,consist of 3 Values only(12,36,60)
  • Occupation: Job of The Borrower ,Over 60 Jobs Values Including;Teacher,Accountant,Computer Programmer ,student etc
  • EmploymentStatus: Employment Status Of the Borrower which have the following values ;Full-time,Employed, Part-time, Not employed,Self Employed,Retired ,Other.
  • IsBorrowerHomeowner: If Borrower Owns a Home ,Takes a Boolean Value ,Either True Or False.
  • Recommendations: Number of recommendations the borrower had at the time the listing was created,Consist of 16 Unique Values ,with a minimum value of 0 And Maximum Value of 39
  • IncomeRange: Income Range Of the Borrower at the time of The loan Application,over 8 categories which ranges from 0-100k+ dollars and also include values such as ; Not employed and Not displayed.
  • IncomeVerifiable:Takes a Boolean value ascertaining whether The Borrower has documents supporting their stated Income
  • StatedMonthlyIncome: A numerical Value Indicating the Monthly Income Of the Borrower as at the time the Loan application was put in.
  • LoanOriginalAmount : Numerical value of The loan amount that was given.
  • LoanStatus : Consist of Values stating The outcome of a loan such as Completed,ChargedOff,Cancelled etc
  • MonthlyLoanPayment: Scheduled amount to be paid back to the loan company monthly ,ranging from 0-2252 Dollars.
  • BorrowerRate: The Borrower's interest rate for this loan in percentages represented as Decimals , a float Datatype.
  • DebtToIncomeRatio:Percentage Of Borrower's Income That goes Back to paying The loan ,a Float data type ranging from 0 to 10.01
  • ListingCategory: Consist of Exactly 20 Categories indicating The reason for a loan application

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

The Main Feature Of Interest in This Dataset is the LoanStatus Variable,It is The aim of the Analysis To 
know The factors resposnsble for each loan Outcome .

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

The 17 Variables picked are all expected  to be pivotal to the analysis ,but Variables such as 
ListingCategory,IncomeRange,IncomeVerifiable,Recommendations,EmploymentStatus,IsBorrowerHomeowner,Term and 
DebtToIncomeRatio are expected to take the cherry.

Engagement Ring,Cosmetic Procedure, Baby&Adoption,Boat,Green Loans, RV falls In  The Bottom reasons Prosper Loan were 
taken.
It's quite Interesting people Take loan To embark on Green project to sustain and Make The Environment 
Friendly(Green Loan),and also for Vacations,Getting a Boat,Wedding,Engagement Ring and Baby&Adoption.

Were there any interesting or surprising interactions between features?¶

Owning a Home was  earlier suspected to  be pivotal in The Completion of a Loan, But That wasnt The Case when The 
IsBorrowerHomeowner Variable Was explored along with Other variables such as DebtToIncomeRatio,LoanOutcome,
MonthlyLoanOutcome and LoanOriginalAmount.It was Found out To have The same Distribution with Borrowers that arent 
Homeowners.

Conclusions¶

Borrowers with a Non Available value for their ListingCategory and EmploymentStatus,Not Displayed value for their 
IncomeRange are prone to Default on loans .Homeowners and Non Homeowners have about the same distribution in Loan
Completion and Defaults .The more number of Recommendations a Borrower gets The more Likely They will complete 
their loan.Borrowers with Good DTI Tend To Complete Their Loans .Loans with a 1 year Duration have the highest 
completion rate with little Defaults .Borrowers With a ListingCategory of Auto and Auto related values  such as 
Motorcycles ,Boats ,RV  also have a good Completion rate.
